      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FIRE BOLT B (5) has scored at his last two starts, most recently by 0.8 lengths over 796m at Sunland Park (Dirt). That continued the very strong form this campaign, with two wins from three outings. Can measure up again. HEZAMONZTER (4) showed little early speed and was always well back last start when eighth, beaten 14 lengths, over this journey at Group 2 level at Remington Park (Dirt). Has the talent to put the recent poor run behind him. JUMP GO GONE (1) last appeared when successful by half a length over 796m at Lone Star Park (Dirt) seven months ago, the only time he went to the races last prep. Has the pace to be in a prominent position from the outset. Winning claims on best figures. BIG LEW LOVE (2) returns from a spell of 18 months and did score first-up when last in work in Group 3 class at Will Rogers Downs (Dirt) over 796m. Lines up for the first time for the Bradley Bolen stable.",
